    rdau:P61101 "<a href='http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/nb98039922'>LCNAF</a>, katsottu 8.9.2025 (King, Charles, 1952-; Sources, found: Design of curved steel, 2001:t.p. (Charles King) BL AL sent 18 Dec. 2001, found: BL AL recd. 2 Jan. 2002(Charles M. King, born 17 Jan. 1952))"@fi,
        "<a href='https://www.linkedin.com/in/charles-king-8021b935/'>LinkedIn</a>, katsottu 3.9.2025 (Charles King, Senior Steel Specialist COWI, Banbury, England, United Kingdom: My primary expertise is in the stability and strength of steel structures, both bridges and buildings. My design experience also includes aluminium for bridges, reinforced concrete, masonry, timber and aerospace structures of carbon fibre composites and aluminium. I have been a member of the sub-committee for Structural Steel for the Canadian bridge design standard CAN/CSA S6 and the BSI committees for steel buildings and composite buildings. I am a guest member of the European committee for the stability of structural steelwork, ECCS/TC8, on which I was the UK representative for several years. I am author and joint author of several design guides published by the Steel Construction Institute, Ascot, UK, on the stability and strength of steel structures and double-skin composite construction.)"@fi,
        "Design of curved steel / Charles King, David Brown, [2001]"@fi ;
