    rdaa:P50411 "King, Charles E. (Charles Everett), 1934-2016"@fi ;
    rdau:P61101 "<a href='https://limnology.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/silnews69.pdf'>In memoriam - Charles King / Terry Snell [ja muita] // SIL news, v. 69 (January 2017):</a> sivut 21-22 (Charles E. King, Professor Emeritus at Oregon State University, died September 5th [2016] in Alaska at age 82.)"@fi,
        "<a href='https://www.legacy.com/us/obituaries/gazettetimes/name/charles-king-obituary?id=13552954'>Charles King obituary / Legacy.com</a>, katsottu 3.9.2025 (Charles Everett King: March 8, 1934 - Sept. 4, 2016 Charles Everett King was born in Chicago on May 8, 1934, and died at age 82 on Sept. 4, 2016, in Juneau, Alaska. ... Charles taught biology and did research at Yale University, the University of Illinois and the University of South Florida. In 1977 he accepted the position as Chair of the Department of Zoology at Oregon State University. ... Although he continued to do research for many years, Charles retired from the university in 2002. Charles was an evolutionary biologist. With sophisticated mathematical models and field and laboratory work, he studied the population dynamics of rotifers, a form of zooplankton, to learn about genetic changes within populations and between species.)"@fi ;
